column9: hey moblet!
g'day 50
i see profitability has increased somewhat
Oh Hi, yes, record profit!
i got desynced earlier and didn't bother trying to get back in with 2 others here
ah.
As you can see, I've been working on the first part of the northern mail line putting together some fragmented trackage from Maliton all the way to Malliham
haven't looked yet, still tackling the mail west of Renham
Oh yeah, west of renham is a big job, and I don't yet have all of the tracks needed to start service up there yer
*yet, but I am making some progress
i was planning on running express mail trucks from interchanges to Renham
just like SE of Heppbury, which is very profitable
Ok. The only reason they are profitable there, though, is because the road is high speed.
The only place there is some good road is south of malliwell
oh, ok
did you have any locations in mind for interchanges, before I set up routes?
nope.
i can start off with trucks and you can put the trains in when you do
tbh, I don't know if I have any plans for trains in that area
and If I do get them, they'll pretty much just parallel schland's line
so you're happy for the mail to go by truck?
i can see a potential mail rail route
maybe looping up to Oakstead
yeah, thats what I was thinking
Let me see what the situation is up there and see if I can throw down a line easily
from Renham mail station run along the southern edge of Renham
station around 368,448
then around southern edge of Mallichester
I would think just build a trunk line down into the area from the north and handle east-west traffic by truck
a mail-only line could be single or mostly single track
yeah, there is some timber that might be useful there...
Schland seems to have lots of spare capacity around there, maybe you could do a deal
191, 391 screams "no" to me....
We have been bitter rivals in this game all the way...
were those last co-ords right?
i just nearly drowned
I build a car shop chain, he comes in and double serves everything right away
hmmm, was that the only instance?
oh no. Just go around the map...
Of course, I've done it to him too...
as one would
it must be especially bitter knowing that you've grown to three times their size
but I at least try to do it only as part of a larger hub setup, not just direct point to point competition
And that for 70 years he was much larger than me!
But in the last 130 years, I have gone ahead
another option is to put down a highway for the mail
railway already in progress
cool
lol!
